//     OR par_haircut (>15% drop, cross-BDC corroborated) OR spread_cut
//     (>50bps cut). Closer to industry definitions of "modified loan".
// Loans whose first observation in our dataset is already PIK are excluded
// from both numerator and denominator — no prior cash-pay state to compare to.
//
//   new_mods         count of loans flipping cash → PIK this quarter (narrow)
//   cured            count of loans flipping PIK → cash this quarter
//   any_mods         count of loans with ANY modification signal (broad)
//   mat_extend       maturity-extension component of any_mods
//   par_haircuts     >15% par-drop component (cross-BDC corroborated)
//   spread_cuts      >50bps cash-rate-cut component
//   n_eligible       loans with a prior observation
//   pct_new          100 * new_mods / n_eligible
//   pct_any_mod      100 * any_mods / n_eligible
//   pct_new_cost     100 * sum(cost of new_mods) / sum(cost of eligible)  ← narrow
//   pct_any_mod_cost 100 * sum(cost of any_mods) / sum(cost of eligible)  ← BROAD HEADLINE
